          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">
          <strong>Rank:</strong> #1st in the world today</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">
          <strong>About:</strong> CEO and chairman of LVMH, Arnault has transformed luxury with brands like Louis Vuitton, Dior, and Tiffany & Co. Known for his meticulous approach, he acquired Christian Dior in the 1980s and built the world’s largest luxury empire. Arnault’s influence spans high fashion, cosmetics, and luxury spirits, and his family members hold critical roles within LVMH.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">
          <strong>Need to Know:</strong> Arnault and LVMH hold a 40% stake in the private equity firm L Catterton, which manages over $30 billion in assets, including investments in brands like Birkenstock and Equinox.​</p>
          
